The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 IT in laggard zone schools

 A STAFF REPORTER

 Calcutta Sept. 20: Everonn Systems India, a Chennai-based company, will teach computers to school students in three Bengal districts, including the backward Purulia and West Midnapore.

 According to a six-year agreement signed between the company and the school education department today, Everonn will create IT infrastructure and impart education in 555 schools in East and West Midnapore and Purulia. 

 Everonn will build computer labs, design curriculum and course materials, recruit and train teachers and help in the automation of school administrative systems.




